			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Adding a third to my duo... but what?<a name="57429"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 18 04 10:39 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Ok, I 2-box a cleric with my bard whenever my wife doesnt feel like playing, but I recently aquired another comp and will set up another EQ account to add to that mix, making it a 3-some (pardon the term). My question is, what class would make the perfect complement to the abilities my wifes cleric and my bard bring to the table? I am capable of tanking with the bard, though I havent tried it since the supposed nerf to chant aggro. I used to be able to tank with just my normal buffs and such with the 2-box in place.
<br />

<br />
With the new change, do I need a &quot;real&quot; tank? A knight class? Or should I go with my original Idea and go the shammy/bst route?I was originally thinking of a BST because his pet wont steal aggro from me, and he has almost the same buffs as shamans at high levels, along with haste/slow.
<br />

<br />
What are your takes on the situation, and if you make a suggestion, back it up with abilities and what roles they would fill, thanks!!</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%">Impresario Amedaius Bladewhisper, 70 ladies' broken hearts and 240 aa meetings. http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=851398</span></td>
