		</table></td><td class="PanelBodyAlternate" valign="Top"><table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3" border="0" width="100%">
			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Adding a third to my duo... but what?<a name="57433"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 18 04 11:34 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>A beastlord would likely be the best choice. Suitable dps without having to rely on clicking nukes, the ability to tank with minimal maintance (a couple poison dots and he'll hold aggro relatively easily, particularly with his pet taunt on), buffs well enough to replace a shaman and provides a slow almost as good. Not quite as good a backup healer as the shaman but it is unlikely that would become necessary with the cleric.
<br />

<br />
Hybrids tanks (shadowknight, paladin, ranger if you're not fighting anything too powerful) would be my backup choice. The hybrids provide low maintenance aggro, shadowknights and rangers about even on the dps scale depending on available weapons and mana regen gear (shadowknight nukes are faster and hence provide larger burst dps compared to rangers losing their dual wielding damage over 1.9 seconds). Paladins provide superior mitigation when necessary through their stuns as well as relatively instant backup healing.
<br />

<br />
The last choice would be some form of dps. Perhaps a mage or a wizard for snare. Mages tend to be superior dps over long periods of time until the wizards gets enough mana regen that aggro becomes their limiting factor. Wizards also provide snare and ports, mages get resist debuffs and to summon sandwiches to pacify non-kos mobs~. Druids may also work but provide inferior dps to either wizards or mages (they become equal to mages when near maxed offensive spell AA), though they have a better snare, backup healing, and ports.
<br />

<br />
Warriors, rogues, berserkers, monks, enchanters, necromancers  tend to be too 'high maintenance' in my opinion to work as a third bot. They mostly involve clicking buttons at short intverals which would cause problems when you're maining a bard. The pure melees in particular don't really provide anything more than dps at the cost of a lot of work.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%">&nbsp;&nbsp;Hunter Sirioh <br>
