				<td colspan="2"><span>I'd say necro or mage.  For all the same reasons other people have suggested a pet caster.  Also, both will add HUGE dps to your otherwise poor dps combo (no bad on you).  A necro/mage pet will most likely tank better than you do, and has a taunt.  Both classes lend themselves well to 2 or 3 boxing and each has their usefulness in other arenas.  CoH, summoned items, serious nukage for the Mage &amp; snare, mez &amp; slow undeads, dots &amp; twitch for the necro.  Not to mention FD and backup rez on the necro.  That' can't be underestimated.  Of course a warrior is also a good option, but warriors and melee classes in general are very gear dependent for performance where a pet is expendable cannon fodder that doesn't require much gear.</span></td>
