				<td colspan="2"><span>Oh, I'm there, and beyond.  I can hit 1500 attack quite easily.  But I seriously doubt anyone is gonna let me try to KS them.  On a side note, if the group has a Monk, Rogue, or Wizard you can hang up the KS idea.  Unless they are very poorly geared.  And if You're in BoT that shouldn't be the case.  Or the group was a less than standard group setup.  But any group with a healer, Slower, Tank, and 3 DPS will not be KSed by a lone Ranger.  I have done it to lower level (60ish) groups on accident a few times, but never a decently AA/Geared group who was actually trying to kill a mob.
<br />

<br />
A Ranger is my Main lvl 65 Hunter with 127AA, Featherwood, GoTF, 1400 unbuffed attack blaah blaah blaah.
<br />

<br />
If the group is a properly built EXP group that isn't gonna happen.  If it does, then I hold tight to my word that they aren't trying too hard.  We are a casual guild, and even equally AAed and Geared Rogues and Monks can outdamage me Except maybe trueshot, but they toss in their discs and I don't stand a chance.  If they know you are trying to KS them, it isn't gonna happen. 
<br />

<br />
But on a side note, I was offtanking a Mob in BoT (You know the lower level Elemental critters) and when you could actually target the mob the group was fighting, pull agro on the add place the add betwen you and your target, and your arrows would hit the add for double damage at point blank range because it was getting hit with the shots meant for the other mob.  Can't do it since DX9 though<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-6.gif" border="0" alt="Sad" hspace="2" /> I did it to see if it worked, and sure enough, I killed my mob about the same time they killed theirs albiet a LB mob.  TS of course<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-2.gif" border="0" alt="Big Smile" hspace="2" />.  I dunno if SoE ever caught onto that, but not that it mattered, people didn't make it a habit.  Rangers deffinately aren't known for their offtanking uberness..
<br />

<br />
The suckiness starts kicking into Rangers anywhere passed PoP. In GoD we make good pet snarers, and can weaponshield the name while hoping the pets take it out before weaponshield wears off, but that is about it.
<br />

<br />
Pre-Elemental though Rangers are VERY viable in a DPS role.  And Snare is always a good thing to have around, as well as easy Macroable DPS.  And there is also SoE, Invis as needed.
<br />

<br />
Ranger and Chanter duos = OWNAGE.  For those interested, I'll cross post a message on Charm rotations that is quite fun if you know a Ranger and a Chanter who like to have fun every now and again.  Adding a Bard to the group to hold mez the mobs as the Ranger pulls them would = an ENDLESS supply of Pets and Mobs to play with, and get EXP from.  </span></td>
